4.9/5  rDev +10.9%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Bomber poured into a snifter. No bottle date or abv but it looks like it's a 2016 vintage from the artwork.
Pour is complete perfection. Totally dark with a milk chocolate colored two finger head that slows goes down. Really nice lacing and the head lingers even after 5 minutes of pouring it. Incredible. 
Smell is ridiculous also. Roasted coffee, chocolate, vanilla, brown sugar, hickory spice. Blown away.
Taste is unsurprisingly amazing. Huge chocolate and molasses, roasted malt, creamy vanilla, oak / wood, and a lovely bitter coffee bean flavor. I'm really struggling not giving this a perfect score in the taste category. 
Feel is perfect in my opinion. Thick with very little carbonation. The creamy head makes for an amazing mouthfeel.
Overall this is easily my favorite Russian Imperial Stout I've ever had. Honestly may be the best beer I've ever had. This is a flawless beer to me and an immaculate example of a RIS. 934 charactersaoampm, May 01, 2017
